57.1	Image_sensor	Image sensor	An image sensor is a device that converts an optical image into an electronic signal. It is used mostly in digital cameras and other imaging devices. Early analog sensors were video camera tubes, most currently used are digital charge-coupled device (CCD) or complementary metal–oxide–semiconductor active pixel sensors.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5d/Ccd-sensor.jpg/230px-Ccd-sensor.jpg
